{"type":"text","timestamp":1775620696107,"sessionID":"ses_294c9a376ffenBvUcB7jp97ECf","part":{"id":"prt_d6b3d83dd001MB2czfM4pbzK29","messageID":"msg_d6b3d6dca001GusEp45F6DYVe5","sessionID":"ses_294c9a376ffenBvUcB7jp97ECf","type":"text","text":"The bar label `'20'` has its x-position stored as a 1-d numpy array `[20.21]` instead of a scalar. This is from `show_counts=True` — upsetplot annotates bars with their count values using `ax.text(...)` and is passing a 1-d array where a scalar is expected. Let me check if a newer version of upsetplot fixes this:","time":{"start":1775620696106,"end":1775620696106}}}
